  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:27-28",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 4:27-28",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Those officers — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Named above, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They lacked nothing — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "they suffered nothing to be lacking ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to any man that came to Solomon’s table, but plentifully provided all things necessary. This is repeated to show their diligence, exactness, and care, which was remarkable; especially since they took care of his stables as well as of his house, as it follows in the next verse. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Barley also and straw — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Barley was anciently horse-corn, as appears by many places in Homer. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For the horses and dromedaries — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Hebrew word, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "rechesh, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "signifies swift horses, as Abarbinel thinks; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Esther 8:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; but others take them for mules. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Where the officers were — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Where the beasts were; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for there is no word for officers in the Hebrew. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Every man according to his charge — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which lasted for a month every year.",
        "children": []
